ommittees work or activities.";i:8;s:156:"The Committee Chair where appropriate guides the committee in proposing products and services that will further the goals and objectives of the association.";i:9;s:191:"The Chairperson is responsible for making sure that each meeting is planned effectively conducted according to the constitution and that matters are dealt with in an orderly efficient manner.";i:10;s:97:"The Chairperson must make the most of all hisher committee members building and leading the team.";i:11;s:76:"Committee chairs The most important influencers of the congressional agenda.";i:12;s:159:"They play dominant roles in scheduling hearings hiring staff appointing subcommittees and managing committee bills when they are brought before the full house.";i:13;s:180:"The Council Committee chair will forward to the City Director Lead those items to be placed on the meeting agenda a minimum of one week in advance of the scheduled monthly meeting.";i:14;s:223:"The City Director Lead will coordinate with staff members the preparation of the agenda to determine whether items will be presented to a Committee or placed on the Councils regular agenda to be considered by the full City.";i:15;s:66:"A committee chair serves as the parliamentary head of a committee.";i:16;s:103:"The chair sets the committees agenda determining whenor in many states whetherbills will be considered.";i:17;s:62:"Other responsibilities of a committee chair typically include.";i:18;s:53:"Calling the committee together to perform its duties.";i:19;s:46:"Presiding and maintaining order over meetings.";i:20;s:100:"N in Communist parties the body responsible for party policy between meetings of the party congress.";i:21;s:78:"In practice it is in charge of day-to-day operations of the party bureaucracy.";i:22;s:29:"Committee of the Whole House.";i:23;s:85:"N in Britain an informal sitting of the House of Commons to discuss and amend a bill.";i:24;s:176:"Among other things committee chairs can hire fire and direct most committee staff refer bills to subcommittees schedule or block hearings and markup and run committee meetings.";i:25;s:207:"The big increase in the number of Conservative MPs following the 2019 election has shifted the allocation of committee chairs which reflects the balance of parties in the Commons in favour of the government.";i:26;s:147:"Of the 28 committees for which chairs are elected Conservative MPs will chair 16 in this parliament up from 13 at the start of the last parliament.";i:27;s:99:"The definition of a Committee Chairman is a person who is elected by a companys board of directors.";i:28;s:68:"This persons job is to preside over the companys committee meetings.";i:29;s:159:"The member who had served on the committee the longest and whose party controlled Congress became chair regardless of party loyalty mental state or competence.";i:30;s:102:"A person gains a committee chair due to being the majority party and being on a committee the longest.";i:31;s:78:"The committees chair has the chief agenda-setting authority for the committee.";i:32;s:87:"In essence the chair identifies the bills or issues on which the committee will try to.";i:33;s:330:"The chairperson also chair chairman or chairwoman is the presiding officer of an organized group such as a board committee or deliberative assemblyThe person holding the office who is typically elected or appointed by members of the group presides over meetings of the group and conducts the groups business in an orderly fashion.";i:34;s:88:"Stress on the penultimate syllable is perhaps by association with Latin comitia comitia.";i:35;s:74:"Please tell us where you read or heard it including the quote if possible.";i:36;s:72:"Noun the presiding officer of a meeting organization committee or event.";i:37;s:74:"The administrative officer of a department of instruction as in a college.";i:38;s:320:"Committee Chairs are elected by their Committee members and provide leadership for Committee activities in support of the profession by representing its members and their needs and concerns through the Division Representatives and communicating with the membersThe Committee Chairs report to the Administrative Division.";i:39;s:83:"A group of people chosen or appointed to perform a specified service or function 2.";i:40;s:120:"Law formerly a person to whom the care of a mentally incompetent person or his or her property was entrusted by a court.";i:41;s:23:"See also receiver2 C15.";i:42;s:29:"From committento entrust -ee.";}}